More specifically, the first step to realizing temperature measurement was to calibrate the temperature dependence of the G-band Raman shift of graphene sandwiched between glass and Cu. As illustrated in Fig. 1b (inset), the glass-graphene-Cu trilayer was allowed to reach thermal equilibrium with a constant temperature stage (estimated accuracy of ±0.5 °C). The graphene was then excited with a visible laser (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
